The paper deals with a game-theoretic setting where individuals choose the precision of the output data they provide, and the linear model estimate is a public good that benefits all individuals. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with statistical data analysis and estimation, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
